# Slack Bolt + Block Kit

All Slack interactivity (slash commands, modals, buttons, view submissions) MUST use
`slack_bolt.App` + `SlackRequestHandler` (Lambda) or the equivalent Bolt adapter.
Do **not** hand-roll Slack HMAC verification or return Slack payloads via raw
`http_response` for slash/interactive traffic.

References: `slackblast/slackblast/app.py`, `qsignups/qsignups/app.py`,
`PAXminer/slack_app.py`. Block Kit helpers: `PAXminer/slack_blocks.py`,
`slackblast/slackblast/utilities/slack/orm.py`, `qsignups/qsignups/slack/inputs.py`.

## Ack rules (3-second window)

- **Good:** empty `ack()` then `client.views_open(...)` for slash → modal.
- **Good:** `ack()` then `client.views_push` / `client.views_update` for `block_actions`.
- **Good:** `ack(response_action="clear"|"errors"|"update", ...)` only on `view_submission`.
- **Bad:** returning `response_action` from `block_actions` (ignored by Slack).
- **Bad:** `ack()` twice in one listener.
- **Bad:** `http_response(200, "")` / JSON-encoding an empty string as the body
  (Slack renders an ephemeral `""` message).

## Latency

Ack in under 3 seconds. Work that takes longer MUST async-invoke a worker Lambda
(`InvocationType="Event"`) or use Bolt lazy listeners. Keep the interactive Lambda
image free of heavy imports (pandas/matplotlib). Keep the Slack front-door Lambda warm
(EventBridge schedule), not provisioned concurrency, on free-tier friendly deploys.

## Block Kit

- All views and outbound messages use Block Kit with a non-empty `text` fallback.
- Channel pickers use `channels_select` (or filtered `conversations_select`), never
  free-text channel ID inputs.
- Respect Slack limits (≈3000 chars/section, ≤50 blocks/message); chunk with helpers.

## Correct exceptions

- Custom non-Slack webhooks (e.g. PAXMiner achievements Function URL with a shared
  secret header) may keep `http_response` + shared-secret verify.
- Chart PNG delivery stays on `files_upload_v2` (not Block Kit).

## On-demand charts/stats (design)

Future slash/`app_mention` handlers on the Slack front door should ack
“Generating…”, async-invoke `ScheduleFunction` (chart worker) with params, and let
the worker `files_upload_v2` to the requesting channel. Never render charts
synchronously on the interactive path.
